<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Bright</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Autumn-foliage town in the Ovens Valley — European trees planted by gold miners turn flame orange in late April / early May. Wandiligong heritage village nearby.]]></description><Point><coordinates>146.956900,-36.729500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Harrietville</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Last village before the climb. 1850s gold-rush bones still visible — old sluice channels in the river. Mount Feathertop (Victoria's second-highest peak) rises behind.]]></description><Point><coordinates>147.066700,-36.883300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mount Hotham</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Australia's third-highest ski resort (1,861 m village; 1,861 m highest sealed point on the road just east of the village). Year-round restaurants; alpine wildflowers in December.]]></description><Point><coordinates>147.142800,-36.978300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Dinner Plain</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Architect-designed alpine village (1986) of corrugated-iron and timber lodges in vernacular styling. Cross-country skiing in winter, mountain biking in summer.]]></description><Point><coordinates>147.243600,-36.983400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Omeo</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Old gold-rush town at 690 m. Once isolated for months by snow each year. The road from Omeo down to the coast is one of Victoria's quietest drives.]]></description><Point><coordinates>147.595000,-37.100600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
